        <button class="accordion">Presentation Summary</button>
    <div class="panel"> 
          <p>Dr. Handler explains the issues in the MCH/public health policy process, including the fact that no one voice acts on behalf of women and children, the presence of class and race issues, and that radical change may have to give way to incremental change. Differences between advocating for mothers/families and children are explained, and strategies for effective communication of these differences are presented.</p>
